<Layout title="Session 113 — Tales of the Radiant Citadel" description="The party reached the High Master's spawning-pits lab — a stone-and-metal structure with an &quot;artichoke-petal&quot; dome roof, already breached from the inside (">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <a href="/studio" class="text-sm text-earth hover:text-ink transition-colors mb-6 inline-block">&larr; Studio</a>

    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black leading-tight mb-2">
      Session 113
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth mb-1">Tales of the Radiant Citadel &middot; May 12, 2026</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-light mb-8">Bluetspur Expedition</p>

    <div class="prose-section text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-12 space-y-4">
      <p>
        The party reached the High Master's spawning-pits lab — a stone-and-metal structure with an &quot;artichoke-petal&quot; dome roof, already breached from the inside (the dome was open because something escaped *out*). Sundr arrived late and dropped in from the roof to join Toven, Virgil, Kiet, and Haru, who were already fighting **ooze-doppelgangers** of themselves — a grey-green hybrid of merged white and black oozes seeping through every wall. Virgil **ate 38 points of radiation** trying to lick a door, Toven walked him back to functional with a string of Lesser Restorations, and Sundr cracked the **monitor station** to learn the lab is an Illithid-civil-war-era WMD facility running **six weapons projects in parallel**: the **Plane Render** (a planar-transit shard whose ongoing chain reaction is the radiation source), the **Bad Thought** (the thought virus — a recursive philosophy that requires a *living biological brain* to carry), the **Elder Brain Dragon** (built to serve a being called **Knebderon**, escaped through the dome, no allegiance, **two viable eggs still on site**), and three un-queried projects (Resident Stones, Psychic Reservoir, Disjunction Gems). The party stacked every possible buff on Kiet — Enhance Ability, Bless, Bardic Inspiration, Guidance, level-4 Healing Word, Second Wind, his permanent +10 Con rad-pill mutation — and sent the &quot;thirsty chicken&quot; on a Metal-Gear-Solid speedrun through the irradiated inner chamber. Kiet lightning-blasted two security doors, sprinted past plane-vision orbs showing La Mortia, Tepest, and Akarin Sengar, and **shattered the energy orb sustaining the radioactive chain reaction** in one anticlimactic shutdown. The plane-tearing shard now glimmers, exposed, at the center of a quiet room. Virgil also opened a cryopod looking for a keycard and woke a **2,000-year-old undead scientist with purple-fire eyes and rotting fists** — crit-killed it back to mostly-dead, looted the keycard, and locked it back in the pod. Session ended with the radiation off, the shard accessible, and the &quot;bad fuck&quot; (Bad Thought) confirmed as still in the lab, awaiting a volunteer's skull.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Highlights</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm text-ink-light leading-relaxed space-y-2 mb-12 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Cold Open — Sundr Drops In</strong> — Erik arrived late; Sundr started the session standing on the lab's metal roof, separated from the party.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">&quot;Slurp Slurp Slurp&quot; — Investigation Roll on a 5</strong> — Sundr advances 25-30 ft into the central monitor room. Asks for an investigation check. Sam (transcription typo): &quot;Make an aviation roll.&quot; Sundr rolls a **5.**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Kiet Commands the White Ooze to Leave</strong> — The original **white ooze** (Kiet's &quot;child&quot; from a prior session, the one with the line on his memories) decides it doesn't want to be there.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Virgil Licks the Door (38 Damage in 8d6 of Poison)</strong> — Virgil grabs a fake-Haru ooze doppelganger; instant pop. Sam: **&quot;She will turn to ooze in your hands, and you're just covered, slicked with this white porn shit, like, running down your face down your front.&quot;**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr's Paranoia — &quot;Are You Real?&quot;</strong> — Toven rounds a corner, sees Sundr. Toven (testing): **&quot;Hey, buddy. Is that you? What's something weird from our history? What's our rat's name?&quot;** Sundr passes the doppelganger sniff test.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Toven Blasts the Door Panel; the Cryopod Bunker</strong> — Toven, having had it with Virgil licking radioactive surfaces, casts **Call Lightning** on the door panel — 3d10 (Erik rolled for him: 10, 9, 5). &quot;You blast the fuck out of that door panel.&quot; Door springs open onto a bunker room with **four sealed cryopods.**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Virgil and the Undead Scientist</strong> — Virgil, still blinded/poisoned/weakened, &quot;desperately crawls&quot; toward the pods. Sam: **&quot;Get into the pods. Weird machines got you into this mess. Weird machines can certainly get you out of it.&quot;**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr at the Monitor Station — The Six Weapons Projects</strong> — Sundr disengages from the buff plan and heads back to the **monitoring station** in the outer lab. Sam: &quot;This is clearly a monitoring station to oversee the various experiments being done in this building.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr's Chromatic Orb — Empowered, Transmuted, Radiant</strong> — Two small hybrid grey-green oozes converge on Sundr at the monitor. He casts **Chromatic Orb** (1st-level slot, no upcast).</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The &quot;Thirsty Chicken&quot; Buff Stack</strong> — Erik attempted to rules-lawyer Enhance Ability under 2024 rules (one stat only); Sam: **&quot;Fuck you, 2024. I'm not gonna care about those rules.&quot;** Erik: **&quot;Fuck you, 2024. Let's suit.&quot;**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Kiet's Run — The Climax</strong> — Kiet uses **Borrow the Power** (channel divinity equivalent), activates draconic wings, and **flies** into the radiation room.</li>
    </ul>

